This paper deals with Markov Logic Networks (MLNs) and their extension to quantified MLNs, which are used for statistical relational learning and reasoning. The paper discusses the limitations of MLNs in expressing certain types of statistics and proposes a solution through the introduction of statistical universal quantifiers. This makes the paper relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SI), and databases (cs.DB).
